        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 30 at 1:31PM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 131 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated strong thunderstorms along a
line extending from 2 miles northeast of Howe to 8 miles south of
Lake Wister State Park. Movement was southeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Patterson...                      Hodgen...
Heavener...                       Howe...
Poteau...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
